AWKA  – Mr. Chuka Nnabuife, an Ihia­la-born renowned journalist, author and cultural ambassa­dor of Nigeria from Anambra State has expressed passion about the development and economic advancement of the Ihiala Local Government Area. Nnabuife especially as Nnabuife who stated this in his office in Awka during an exclusive interview with Daily Independent said he believes that the council area will thrive a lot with democratic instruments and affirmed that Ihiala is situat­ed in the middle of Igboland. 2023: North East, North Central Legislators Back Yahaya Bello BREAKING: Sanwo-Olu Reinstates Suspended LASU Registrar, Amuni He said Ihiala may not particularly be a trading town but it is surrounded by trad­ing cities such as Onitsha, Nnewi and extends to Aba in Abia State, adding that Ihiala is a location that requires a lot of smart thinking and smart legislative instruments to po­sition it where it should be. Nnabuife expressed strong belief that Ihiala is a place with quality deposits of hu­man capital but expressed worry that the human re­source is not being harnessed to help the young ones grow and develop themselves fur­ther. According to him, Ihiala is one of the oldest divisions created in the history of Nige­ria yet it has remained a sin­gle division since its creation when its contemporaries like Nnewi, Aguata, Onitsha and some others have been divid­ed into two or more divisions. Nnabuife who is current­ly the Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Anambra Newspapers and Printing Corporation noted that Ihiala is in dire need of the right policies and legis­lative instruments to get its proper position in the polity.